but it was true bootstrapping, track0 sector0 was loaded into ram, then executed, so whatever there was on the disk, control was handed over to it, if it was an apple dos disk, these first 256 bytes would take care of pulling in the rest of the dos, then giving the user a prompt again

a diskless apple][ would give you a command prompt, could do very few commands, and had an 'integer basic' interpreter with it - adding and booting disks added disk-specific commands, like loading or saving, or showing a disk's content
